answers.answer: Can you please clarify something for me...Are 2 of your NATIVE arteries 100% blocked nowORAre 2 of your bypass conduits 100% blocked?You say Arteries, which makes me assume you are referring to your Native coronary arteries, am I correct?

question: I had quadruple bypass surgery in Sept 08.  I have diabetes also.  Yesterday I had an angiogram and was told that 2 of the arteries are 100% blocked.  My cardiologists doesn't want to see me for 6 months, is this normal procedure.
title: 100% blockage
